Utterances.UttText: S: Gerry Cage is a 55 yo F with HTN presenting to clinic three days after an episode of chest pain.

Phrases.PhraseText: a 55 yo F with HTN presenting
to clinic three days after an episode of chest pain.

Utterances.UttText: The chest pain occurred while she was walking groceries to her car.
She experienced the pain in the  middle of her chest.

Phrases.PhraseText: the pain in the  middle of her chest.

Utterances.UttText: Describes the pain as a deep, aching pain.
Pain lasted for about 5-10 minutes and resolved after she sat in her car.
Endorses feeling faint and a sensation of "having her breath taken away."
Denies diaphoresis or limb numbness/tingling.
Endorses past history of similar "chest twinges" that also occur with exertion.
Denies chest pain at rest.
Of note, patient smokes cigarettes 1 PPD x 30 years.
Works a sedentary job and walks dog for exercise.
4-5 coffees per day.
Strong family history of cardiovascular disease with father MI @ 40 and mother PE @ 60.

Phrases.PhraseText: Strong family history of cardiovascular disease

Utterances.UttText: O:  VS: BP 150/92 HR: 85 RR: 14 T: 98F Gen appearance: No acute distress Cardio: Regular rate, normal rhythm.
Normal S1/S2.
No murmurs, rubs, or gallops.
Radial pulses 2+ bilaterally.
Good cap refill.
Grossly well perfused.
Pulmonary: Normal WOB, lungs CTAB, no cyanosis, no clubbing.
MSK: No chest wall tenderness.
A:  Gerry Cage is a 55 yo F with HTN and tobacco use presenting after episode of sternal chest pain with exertion.

Phrases.PhraseText: tobacco use presenting after episode of sternal chest pain

Utterances.UttText: Physical exam normal today.
Strong family history of cardiovascular disease.

Phrases.PhraseText: Strong family history of cardiovascular disease.

Utterances.UttText: Given HTN, tobacco use, and family hx, patient is at risk for coronary artery disease and I am concerned this was an episode of anginal chest pain.

Phrases.PhraseText: at risk for coronary artery disease

MappingCandidates.CandidatePreferred: CDISC SDTM Coronary Artery Disease Risk Terminology

Phrases.PhraseText: an episode of anginal chest pain.

Utterances.UttText: DDx: Stable angina - pain is substernal occurring with exertion NSTEMI/STEMI GERD  Costochondritis - less likely given no chest wall tenderness  P: EKG with troponin BMP/CBC  Lipid panel - if elevated LDL add moderate intensity statin  Consider adding beta blocker or calcium channel blocker
